('3796', '331', 'description', '<h3>Description</h3>\r\nBall valves are mainly used when fast operation is required in the oil & gas, petrochemical, nuclear and power plants. They are installed in the pipelines, in the power generation plants, in the water treatment and cryogenic applications.\r\n\r\n<h3>Design</h3>\r\naccording to API 6D, ASME B16.34\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Floating and Trunnion-mounted design</li>\r\n<li>Side entry and Top entry construction</li>\r\n<li>Full and Reduced bore</li>\r\n<li>Metal to metal and Soft seal seated</li>\r\n<li>Anti blow out stem</li>\r\n<li>Double block and bleed\r\n<li>Single or Double piston effect seats</li>\r\n<li>Sub-sea and Criogenic executions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFire safe tested API 6fa, API 607, ISO 10497\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Range of production</h3>\r\n\r\n<small>All sizes and ratings available on demand.\r\nWe can supply ball valves with manual levers, gear operators, electric, pneumatic or hydraulic actuators.</small>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Construction Materials</h3>\r\nMain casted and forged materials:\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Body</strong>\r\nForged carbon steel, stainless steel, special and exotic alloys. all casted steel materials for “top entry” type.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Trim</strong>\r\nForged or pressed carbon steel, stainless steel, special and exotic alloys.</p>'),
